10:
Gaaah! What's the big idea?! Don't
just sit on me outta nowhere!
20: Come on, get up. Let's do something.
23:
Can't you go play in the water? Build
a sand castle or whatever?
29:
Could've fooled me with the way
you were actin' yesterday...
36: Why don't you let Daddy carry you?
40:
Awww, you're gonna hurt Daddy's
feelings!
48: Alice... I'll look after you today.
49:
You can even treat me as your
father if you'd like.
58:
I-I only meant that I am the oldest
here! So naturally...
66:
I only wanted to let you know that,
should you want a companion
today, I can be one for you.
71:
Ugh, I don't need you treating me
like a little kid too.
76:
Actually... If Light wants to babysit
you, why don't we let him?
80: Hmm, now that you mention it.
93:
Don't wear yourself out too fast,
Pops.
132: I cannot... go on... any farther...
153: Fine, I'll just go on my own then!
157: Hold it right there, little lady!
159:
This is a hunting park! We got all
sorts of monsters cooped up in
there!
160:
A little kid like you will get eaten up
in seconds!
162: Oh yeah? We'll see about that.
165:
Did you not hear a word I just said?
Listen to your elders, kid—
168: Hey... Hey, hey, hey! What the heck?!
187:
It can't be... Is she the Marine
Nightmare?
189:
Alice is pretty infamous no matter
where she goes, huh...
192:
Eh, let her have her fun. She'll be too
wiped to complain much tonight.
197:
What part of this exudes maturity,
exactly?
201:
Light, did you see that? Wasn't I
amazing?
205: Yes, I saw everything. You did well.
209: Now, what should we do after this?
